Text.Value: Ever since we seized the moment and won the day, I cannot say I'm aware of the orb's presence anymore... a most curious sensation, and a most unexplained one to boot.

EditorData.NodeContext: Gale helped to save the day without using the orb to sacrifice himself. Catching up with his former companions on his life after an absence of some months. Relieved and thoughtful. Happy and forward-looking at the end; a great burden's been lifted.

Text.Value: But that's all gone now - I've got to move on, find some place for myself.
I'm hoping to find some place I can settle down and stay close to them. Somewhere quiet, where they can find peace, and gaze at the night sky...
|Been razing the hells and free the slaves. Had a blast doing it too|
|Something about Baldur's Gate and ruler.|
I've been with my parents, mostly - making up for lost time, caring for them how I can. I don't know if I'll ever truly shake off all that Shar did to us - made me do to us... but I'll try.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shadowheart abandoned Shar in Act 2 and was on a quest throughout Act 3 to save her parents, which she did. Catching up with her former companions on her life after an absence of some months. Undaunted and forward-looking. Dismissive of Shar.

Text.Value: Quite the storied adventures, indeed.
|Beep boop|
|They look to me as a kind of leader. It's very sweet, actually.|

I gave them the release they asked for, freed myself from Shar's grasp, just as they wished for... but plenty of times, I think I'd trade that to be able to see them again, talk to them again. There's so much only they could have told me.
|I feel for my brothers and sisters. I hope one day I'll be strong enough to free them.|
I've faced her spite before, and lived. Now I have my family by my side as well. She can try to hurt us... but we'll persevere. It's what we do.
I refuse to believe it's been so long. It seems more like a handful of moments since we won the day... and I won the crown.

EditorData.NodeContext: Gale helped save the day but also seized an item of vast magical power  that could help him defy the gods themselves. Catching up with his former companions on his life after an absence of some months. A little fervent and obsessive. Speaks in positive terms about his new endeavour, but others may fear he's heading down a dangerous path.

Text.Value: |And trying to keep an eye on thousands of vampire spawn terrorising the Underdark.|
Now is the time to spread her word: so many have suffered greatly, gripped by pain and loss... they will rush to the Dark Lady's embrace.
But I'm sure I'm not the only one having a good time.
|She had no love for this plane. It's no surprise she isn't here|
I've... I've spent a great deal unravelling what happened - the Chamber of Loss. Shar. My family.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shadowheart abandoned Shar in Act 2 and was on a quest throughout Act 3 to save her parents, but ultimately euthanized them at their request so they and SH could be free of Shar's influence. Catching up with her former companions on her life after an absence of some months. Bittersweet, with a hopeful, forward-looking upswing at the end.

Text.Value: I've been studying it closely ever since - teasing out its power, determining the best way to grasp its potential. Utter focus, near-constant solitude, mere snatched moments of sleep... and yet I have never felt more alive.
The possibilities are beyond comprehension of most mortals... but not for me.
Lady Shar's work is never-ending. I've cleansed the ranks of her followers, leaving only the faithful - the worthy.

EditorData.NodeContext: Shar path outcome - now in charge of Shar's church. Catching up with her former companions on her life after an absence of some months. Busy but relishing it.

Text.Value: Either way, I've spent too long living under that shadow. Now I'm free to return to what truly matters - exploring the unknown, extending mastery of the Weave for all mortals... and catching up on my reading, with Tara curled up in my lap.
I've been with my parents, mostly - making up for lost time, caring for them how I can. Some wounds are slow to heal, and some likely never will...

EditorData.NodeContext: Abandoned Shar at the last moment and saved her parents. Catching up with her former companions on her life after an absence of some months. Philosophical, quietly determined.
EditorData.logicalname: Swerved from Shar last moment, saved parents

Text.Value: |Cazador's still out there.|

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Branch if neither Astarion nor the player ever confronted Cazador

Text.Value: I turned from Shar, but she still likes to twist the knife, now and again. But nothing she does can sour the fact that I have my family again.
|Exploring this world has been enjoyable. I'm glad that I chose to stay here.|
|MINSC BLOCK|
I will not rush it though; I have been burned by the power of Netheril before. It could take years, but when I am ready to act, mortals will no longer need to fear the wrath of gods.
The wars of late have left many with nowhere to turn... and so I have decided to help them make a new place for themselves, in Thaniel's realm, under nature's watch.

EditorData.NodeContext: Catching up with his former colleagues after an absence of several months. Halsin intends to form a commune of sorts to provide a new home for those who suffered during the war against the Absolute. Gamely and passionately rising to the occasion.

Text.Value: Oh, I've been having a marvellous time! After two centuries, I'm finally back in the upper crust and more powerful than ever.
|I've been readjusting to living in the shadows.|
Many lost their homes. Some never had them. Now is the time for us to take care of each other.
There are nine whole wagons of children without families in tow. They are my duty now. 'Daddy Halsin', they call me. Who am I to tell them otherwise?

EditorData.NodeContext: Smiling proudly/with amusement to himself on 'Daddy Halsin'.

Text.Value: |Cazador's been keeping his distance, at least.|
And I can still feel my parents at my side, from time to time. Watching, encouraging... they're at peace, and they want me to be at peace as well.
|I didn't go to the Shar Temple and make a choice about my parents. I'm still alive, but missing something. Still feels like I'm searching...|
|JAHEIRA BLOCK|
|Well since you killed Cazador, I haven't had much else to do.|
Rubbing elbows with the rich and powerful, throwing hedonistic balls, the occasional assassination - it all gets easier when you're secretly a powerful immortal.
But these days I'm mostly just collecting devotees and accumulating power.
Perhaps Mystra has forgiven me, but hasn't deigned to inform me of the fact. Such as it is with gods.

Synopsis: Withers has gathered the companions together one final time as a reunion of sorts 6 months later. They each exposit their various activities. Minthara is not here because she is only present if she is partnered with the player (she is still a speaker here but can change).
